questions.text:
Given this code:

const form = this.fb.group({
  name: ['', Validators.required],
  email: ['', [Validators.required, Validators.email]]
});

How do you check if the 'email' control has a 'required' error?

The following custom validator has a bug. What is it?

export function minAge(min: number) {
  return (control: AbstractControl) => {
    return control.value < min ? { minAge: true } : {};
  };
}

Given this interceptor code:

export const authInterceptor: HttpInterceptorFn = (req, next) => {
  const cloned = req.clone({ setHeaders: { Authorization: 'Bearer token123' } });
  return next(cloned);
};

What does this interceptor do?

Given this directive:

@Directive({ selector: '[appLogger]' })
export class LoggerDirective {
  constructor(private el: ElementRef, private renderer: Renderer2) {}
  @HostListener('click') onClick() {
    this.renderer.setStyle(this.el.nativeElement, 'color', 'red');
  }
}

Why is Renderer2 preferred over directly accessing nativeElement.style?

Given this pipe:

@Pipe({ name: 'truncate', pure: false })
export class TruncatePipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(value: string, length: number): string {
    return value.length > length ? value.slice(0, length) + '...' : value;
  }
}

What is the performance concern with pure: false?
